grid.text: 8. Slide L. to face the waki
8. Slide L to face the waki
of the tsukurimono with lifted L. arm.

captions.translation: [JIUTAI] Indeed, the desolate sound of the wind,
the wicker bamboo fence as in the past.
captions.transcription: Sudo no takegaki arishi yo no.
captions.japaneseScript: 簀戸の竹垣有りし世の。

captions.translation: Please show me your form in a dream
captions.transcription: Yume no sugata wo mise tamae.

captions.translation: I will pray in earnest for your soul.
[SHITE] The moon, uncertain of the mountain ridge as it went
captions.transcription: [SHITE] Yama no ha no kokoro mo shirade yuku tsuki wa,
captions.japaneseScript: ［シテ］山の端の。心も知らで行く月は

captions.translation: and disappeared in the sky high above without a trace.
captions.transcription: uwa no sora nite taeshi ato no.
captions.japaneseScript: 上の空にて絶えし跡の。

captions.translation: [JIUTAI] Though the mountain dweller's fence has fallen into ruin, from time to time
captions.transcription: [JIUTAI] Yamagat'n no kakio aru tomo oriori wa.
captions.japaneseScript: ［地謡］山賤の。垣ほ荒るとき折々は

captions.translation: [SHITE] Show compassion for the wild pink
[JIUTAI] Blossom, if I reaveal the form
captions.transcription: [JIUTAI] Hana no sugata wo mo mamienaba.

captions.translation: [SHITE] Will you pray for my soul ?
[JIUTAI] The vine-covered lattice shutter pushes open,
revealing her form as she steps out.
At the sight tears flow without stopping.
captions.japaneseScript: 見るに涙のとゞまらず。
